Author: incryptico
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] ❣️ SupPorter - World's 1st Crypto Fundraising Platform! ❣️
Body: Will all internal economics run on your token? I mean, say, you raise funds for good in tokens and then its exchange rate falls, or Ethereum rate to USD falls, will that mean that the amounts of funds raised for charity will decrease?

Author: SupPorterInc
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] ❣️ SupPorter - World's 1st Crypto Fundraising Platform! ❣️
Body: Hello incryptico, Good question!  The short answer is no, but certainly we are not immune to the market fluctuations.  Our platform allows organizations to receive multiple forms of currency, and also hold multiple forms of currency.  In general, yes, if they are holding a currency (USA, ETH, The SupPorter Token, Etc...) and that currency's value increases/decreases, then yes, the amount of funds raised would also increase/decrease.  However, The SupPorter Token's price will not be specifically tied directly to any other form form of currency.

Author: ICOs
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] ❣️ SupPorter - World's 1st Crypto Fundraising Platform! ❣️
Body: Where are you incorporated or plan to incorporate? Are you legally registered as a not-for-profit corporation in that country?

Author: SupPorterInc
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] ❣️ SupPorter - World's 1st Crypto Fundraising Platform! ❣️
Body: Hello! We are incorporated in the United Stated in the State of Georgia.  Georgia is actually pretty progressive when it comes to ICOs and we have lots of personal friends in the Secretary of State as well as Governor's Office.  We are fully registered as a 501(c)3 nonprofit incorporated in Georgia as The SupPorter Foundation.  However, the entity conducting the ICO is SupPorter, Inc, which is a Georgia registered for profit corporation.   Happy to answer any other questions!
